er%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2019%2F01%2F17%2Fwhere-millennials-end-and-generation-z-begins%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eborn%20between%201997%20and%202012%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20survey%20indicated%20that%2040%25%20of%20the%20business%20leaders%20surveyed%20think%20recent%20college%20graduates%20are%20unprepared%20to%20enter%20the%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20those%20surveyed%20still%20felt%20they%20were%20at%20least%20somewhat%20prepared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20data-id%3D%5C%22_%2FVx7hy8UDRzqsew65837D%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22interactive%5C%22%20data-title%3D%5C%22College%20Grads%20Unprepared%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20survey's%20methodology%2C%20a%20business%20leader%20was%20defined%20as%20someone%20aged%2030%20to%2060%20making%20at%20least%20%2475%2C000%20in%20household%20income%20and%20currently%20working%20as%20a%20C-Level%20executive%2C%20HR%20manager%2C%20director%2C%20president%2C%20owner%2Fpartner%2C%20or%20senior%20management%20at%20a%20company%20with%20more%20than%2010%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20poor%20perception%20of%20recent%20Gen%20Z%20graduates%20on%20some%20business%20leaders%20may%20even%20be%20impacting%20their%20hiring%20decisions%2C%20the%20survey%20indicated.%20Looking%20at%20the%2040%25%20of%20business%20leaders%20surveyed%20who%20said%20recent%20graduates%20are%20unprepared%20to%20enter%20the%20workforce%20(500%20of%20the%201%2C243%20total%20respondents)%2C%20a%20whopping%2094%25%20of%20that%20subset%20told%20Intelligent%20that%20they%20have%20avoided%20hiring%20them%3A%207%25%20said%20that%20they%20always%20avoid%20hiring%20the%20Gen%20Z%20grads%2C%2027%25%20said%20they%20usually%20avoid%20hiring%20them%2C%2040%25%20said%20they%20%26quot%3Bsometimes%26quot%3B%20do%2C%20and%2020%25%20said%20they%20%26quot%3Brarely%26quot%3B