statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20issued%20by%20the%20Pakistan%20foreign%20ministry%20on%20Sunday%20evening.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20had%20been%20a%20lot%20of%20speculation%20about%20whether%20Islamabad%20would%20allow%20the%20national%20team%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20ICC%20world%20cup%20in%20October-November%2C%20especially%20since%20India%20had%20refused%20to%20send%20its%20team%20for%20Asia%20Cup%20matches%20in%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStating%20that%20Pakistan%20has%20%E2%80%9Cdeep%20concerns%E2%80%9D%20about%20its%20cricket%20team%E2%80%99s%20security%2C%20the%20foreign%20office%20noted%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20conveying%20these%20concerns%20to%20the%20International%20Cricket%20Council%20and%20the%20Indian%20authorities.%20We%20expect%20that%20full%20safety%20and%20security%20of%20Pakistan%20Cricket%20Team%20will%20be%20ensured%20during%20its%20visit%20to%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20further%20claimed%20that%20Pakistan%20believes%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cstate%20of%20bilateral%20relations%20with%20India%20should%20not%20stand%20in%20the%20way%20of%20fulfilling%20its%20international%20sports-related%20obligations%E2%80%9D.%20It%20also%20contrasted%20Pakistan%20as%20having%20shown%20a%20%E2%80%9Cconstructive%20and%20responsible%20approach%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20India%E2%80%99s%20intransigent%20attitude%2C%20as%20the%20latter%20had%20refused%20to%20send%20its%20Cricket%20Team%20to%20Pakistan%20for%20the%20Asia%20Cup%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20relations%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20have%20largely%20been%20hostile%20for%20the%20last%20six%20to%20seven%20years%2C%20diplomatic%20ties%20were%20officially%20downgraded%20in%202019%20when%20the%20Indian%20high%20commissioner%20was%20asked%20to%20leave%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20dissolution%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20constitutional%20autonomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20Najam%20Sethi-led%20Pakistan%20Cricket%20Board%20had%20come%20to%20an%20understanding%20that%20the%20Asia%20Cup%20would%20be%20held%20under%20a%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dawn.com%2Fnews%2F1752482%5C%22%3Ehybrid%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20meant%20that%20the%20matches%20will%20be%20divided%20between%20Pakistan%20and%20another%20neutral%20venue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20effectively%20allow%20India%20to%20take%20part%20in%20the%20Asia%20Cup%20even%20though%20BCCI%20was%20adamant%20that%20the%20Indian%20team%20will%20not%20travel%20to%20Pakistan.%20With%20India%E2%80%99s%20participation%20confirmed%2C%20there%20was%20an%20expectation%20that%20the%20PCB%20had%20given%20a%20tacit%20nod%20to%20the%20national%20cricket%20team%20to%20go%20for%20the%20ICC%20world%20cup.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20change%20at%20the%20helm%20in%20the%20PCB%2C%20there%20seems%20to%20have%20been%20a%20roll%20back%20on%20this%20understanding.%20After%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icc-cricket.com%2Fnews%2F3558110%5C%22%3EWorld%20Cup%20schedule%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20announced%20in%20June%2C%20the%20PCB%20said%20that%20it%20would%20still%20need%20government%20clearance%20for%20the%20tour%20of%20Indian%20cities%20during%20the%20world%20cup.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Pakistan%20has%20now%20confirmed%20its%20participation%2C%20BCCI%20has%20to%20still%20announce%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Ficc-world-cup%2Fworld-cup-schedule-likely-to-be-changed-jay-shah%2Farticleshow%2F102178599.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Erescheduled%20dates%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20matches%2C%20including%20some%20of%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20venues%2C%20less%20than%20two%20months%20before%20the%20start%20of%20the%20World%20Cup.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691376263000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F09153506%2FF0hx0lNaMAExJBn.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Fpakistani-government-says-cricket-team-wil