0charred%20corpses%20and%20limbs.%20It%20was%20difficult%20to%20tell%20who%20was%20alive%20and%20who%20was%20dead%2C%20Rahim%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20little%20boy%20had%20been%20hit%20in%20his%20belly%20by%20a%20metal%20fragment%2C%20and%20wailed%20that%20his%20family%20was%20killed%2C%20his%20uncle%20remembers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stench%20from%20the%20bodies%20was%20overwhelming%2C%20so%20villagers%20scooped%20up%20the%20children%20and%20drove%20the%20injured%20to%20a%20government%20hospital.%20The%20boy%20would%20remain%20there%20for%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20very%20bad%20scene.%20There%20was%20nothing%20left%2C%26quot%3B%20Rahim%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20houses%20were%20blown%20away%2C%20and%20every%20dead%20body%20was%20under%20the%20soil.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20neighbors%20wept%20and%20pulled%20bodies%20from%20the%20rubble%2C%20people%20poured%20in%20from%20neighboring%20towns%20to%20help%2C%20villagers%20recalled.%20Soon%20everyone%20from%20the%20home%20was%20accounted%20for%2C%20either%20living%20or%20dead%20%E2%80%94%20except%20for%20one.%20They%20could%20not%20find%20the%20baby%20girl.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20dug%20through%20the%20dirt%20floor%20of%20the%20home%20with%20shovels%20and%20their%20hands.%20They%20moved%20furniture%20and%20soil.%20They%20were%20worried%20that%20surely%20the%20baby%20%E2%80%94%20only%2040%20days%20old%20%E2%80%94%20was%20stuck%20under%20the%20earth%20or%20the%20debris%20and%20just%20too%20small%20to%20find.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20she%20was%20gone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20CHILD'S%20FATE%20IN%20LIMBO%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20farmer%2C%20his%20wife%20and%20their%20five%20children%20were%20buried%20in%20a%20row%20in%20the%20family%20graveyard%2C%20where%20generations%20of%20kin%20had%20been%20laid%20to%20rest.%20Villagers%20said%20more%20than%20100%20people%20came%20to%20help%20dig%20their%20graves%20in%20the%20hard%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20buried%20the%20foreigners%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than