2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bthrough%20a%20family%20trace%20and%20verification%20process%2C%20that%20the%20child%20was%20Afghan%2C%20not%20'stateless.'%26quot%3B%20So%20when%20the%20government%20of%20Afghanistan%20requested%20the%20child%20be%20transferred%20to%20its%20custody%20to%20be%20returned%20to%20her%20family%2C%20the%20U.S.%20complied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20understood%20at%20the%20time%20that%20all%20appropriate%20procedures%20had%20been%20followed%20under%20Afghan%20law%2C%20and%20that%20remains%20our%20understanding%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20State%20Department%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Masts%20argue%20the%20Afghan%20government%20wrongly%20linked%20the%20child%20to%20the%20family%20without%20DNA%20testing%2C%20pictures%20of%20her%20with%20this%20family%20or%20any%20documentation%20connecting%20her%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoshua%20Mast's%20brother%2C%20lawyer%20Richard%20Mast%2C%20is%20now%20named%20in%20a%20federal%20lawsuit%20filed%20by%20the%20Afghan%20family%20that%20alleges%20the%20Masts%20fraudulently%20claimed%20the%20child%20was%20%26quot%3Bstateless%26quot%3B%20in%20their%20quest%20to%20adopt%20her.%20Richard%20Mast's%20lawyer%2C%20David%20Yerushalmi%2C%20questioned%20why%20an%20innocent%20farmer%20would%20be%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23894831-doc-272-1-richard-emails%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bliving%20in%20the%20same%20compound%20as%20heavily%20armed%20foreign%20fighters.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3EHe%20said%20there%20is%20no%20proof%20the%20orphan%20belonged%20to%20the%20farmer%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Masts'%20efforts%20to%20stop%20the%20U.S.%20government%20from%20turning%20her%20over%20failed%2C%20and%20the%20child%20was%20taken%20to%20the%20farmer's%20brother.%20Since%20he%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20take%20care%20of%20her%2C%20he%20gave%20her%20to%20his%20son%20and%20daughter-in-law%2C%20who%20were%20better%20off%2C%20educated%20newlyweds%20living%20in%20the%20city.%20They%20gladly%20agreed%20to%20raise%20her%20as%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20her%20parents%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20uncle%20told%20AP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20next%2018%20months%2C%20as%20she%20grew%20to%20be%20a%20toddler%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20Joshua%20Mast%20did%20not%20give%20up.%20He%20convinced%20a%20Virginia%20state%20court%20to%20grant%20him%20an%20adoption.%20All%20he%20needed%20was%20to%20get%20her%20on%20U.S.%20soil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELess%20than%20two%20years%20after%20the%20raid%2C%20Mast%20helped%20the%20Afghan%20couple%20and%20the%20toddler%20flee%20as%20the%20country%20collapsed%20and%20the%20Taliban%20took%20over.%20Days%20after%20they%20arrived%20in%20the%20U.S.%2C%20the%20Masts%20worked%20with%20federal%20employees%20at%20a%20refugee%20resettlement%20camp%20to%20take%20custody%20of%20the%20child.%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fafghan-baby-us-marine-custody-battle-b157557538b84b288a0a8415735e24ab%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Afghan%20couple%20are%20suing%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20get%20her%20back%2C%20but%20she%20remains%20in%20limbo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoshua%20Mast%2C%20his%20lawyer%20and%20attorneys%20representing%20the%20Afghan%20couple%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20in%20remote%20Afghanistan%2C%20the%20farmer's%20surviving%20family%20is%20haunted%20by%20all%20they%20saw%2C%20and%20all%20they%20lost.%20When%20his%20brother-in-law%20sees%20his%20nephew%20smile%2C%20he%20thinks%20of%20how%20his%20sister%2C%20now%20dead%2C%20would%20laugh%20when%20he%20teased%20her%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGod%20will%20make%20him%20grow%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bhe%20will%20bring%20life%20to%20this%20house.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20boy%20continues%20to%20struggle%20and%20finds%20it%20hard%20to%20be%20around%20other%20families.%20When%20asked%20if%20he%20remembered%20his%20parents%2C%20he%20began%20to%20cry.%20He%20bit%20his%20lip%20and%20looked%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20girl%20who%20dropped%20her%20baby%20sister%20is%20tormented%20by%20ghosts.%20When%20she%20speaks%20to%20strangers%20covered%20in%20a%20shawl%2C%20she%20is%20so%20small%20and%20frail%20that%20it%20seems%20to%20swallow%20her.%20She%20fidgets%20nervously%20with%20the%20hem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20could%20speak%20perfectly%20before%20the%20soldiers%20came%20that%20night%2C%20but%20now%20she%20stutters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20life%20is%20sad%2C%20my%20heart%20is%20sad%2C%20and%20I%20miss%20my%20parents%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20see%20this%20attack%20every%20night%E2%80%A6.it%20comes%20to%20me%20in%20my%20dreams.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-soldier-may-have-inaccurately-reported-on-raid-in-afghanistan-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691354660000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cff71120f1cf0019cb91fa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-soldier-may-have-inaccurately-reported-on-raid-in-afghanistan-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20child%20was%20found%20after%20a%20raid%20by%20US%20soldiers.%20Afghan%20villagers%20say%20the%20father%20was%20an%20innocent%20farmer%20killed%20in%20the%20raid%20and%20that%20the%20child%20belongs%20with%20the%20family.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Associated%20Press%2CKatie%20Hawkinson%20)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A44%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-soldier-may-have-inaccurately-reported-on-raid-in-afghanistan-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bear%20escapes%20from%20crate%20on%20a%20plane%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691354520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%2