ie-jenner-mini-bratz-collaboration-confuses-fans-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20every%20reported%20case%20where%20police%20mistakenly%20arrested%20someone%20using%20facial%20recognition%2C%20that%20person%20has%20been%20Black%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222861%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20security%20cameras%20attached%20to%20a%20pole%20outside.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cfd96020f1cf0019cb83d7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222145%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20senior%20staff%20attorney%20with%20the%20American%20Civil%20Liberties%20Union%20called%20facial%20recognition%20technology%20in%20law%20enforcement%20%26quot%3Ban%20extremely%20dangerous%20practice.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EFabrizio%20Bensch%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAll%20six%20known%20reports%20of%20false%20arrests%20due%20to%20facial%20recognition%20technology%20were%20made%20by%20Black%20people.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAs%20activists%20have%20warned%20for%20several%20years%2C%20facial%20recognition%20technology%20and%20AI%20can%20exacerbate%20racial%20inequity%20in%20policing.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESeveral%20police%20departments%20across%20the%20country%20use%20the%20technology%2C%20with%20Baltimore%20police%20running%20over%20800%20searches%20last%20year%2C%20one%20expert%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20several%20years%2C%20civil%20liberties%20groups%2C%20tech%20experts%2C%20and%20activists%20have%20warned%20that%20the%20use%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiases-ethics-facial-recognition-ai-mit-joy-buolamwini-2019-1%5C%22%3Efacial%20recognition%20technology%20will%20only%20increase%20racial%20inequities%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20policing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20time%20goes%20on%2C%20it%20is%20becoming%20even%20more%20clear%20that%20these%20warnings%20were%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPorcha%20Woodruff%20%E2%80%94%20a%20mother%20from%20Detroit%2C%20Michigan%20%E2%80%94%20became%20the%20first%20woman%20to%20report%20that%20police%20falsely%20identified%20her%20as%20a%20suspect%20using%20faulty%20facial%20recognition%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F08%2F06%2Ftechnology%2Ffacial-recognition-false-arrest.html%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20is%20now%20the%20sixth%20person%20to%20report%20a%20false%20accusation%20based%20on%20facial%20recognition%20technology%20%E2%80%94%20and%20every%20report%20that%20came%20before%20hers%20was%20filed%20by%20someone%20who%20is%20Black%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Times.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20reviewed%20the%20allegations%20contained%20in%20the%20lawsuit.%20They%20are%20very%20concerning%2C%26quot%3B%20Detroit%20Police%20Chief%20James%20E.%20White%20wrote%20in%20a%20comment%20to%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20taking%20this%20matter%20very%20seriously.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%20%E2%80%94%20months%20after%20Woodruff's%20arrest%20last%20February%20%E2%80%94%20a%20research%20paper%20from%20criminal%20justice%20experts%20Thaddeus%20L.%20Johnson%20and%20Nastasha%20N.%20Johnson%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0740624X22000892%3Fvia%253Dihub%5C%22%3Edemonstrated%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20facial%20recognition%20leads%20police%20departments%20to%20arrest%20Black%20people%20at%20disproportionately%20high%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20this%20results%20from%20factors%20that%20include%20the%20lack%20of%20Black%20faces%20in%20the%20algorithms'%20training%20data%20sets%2C%20a%20belief%20that%20these%20programs%20are%20infallible%20and%20a%20tendency%20of%20officers'%20own%20biases%20to%20magnify%20these%20issues%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scientificamerican.com%2Farticle%2Fpolice-facial-recognition-technology-cant-