adverse%20implications%20on%20press%20freedom%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20statement%20said%20that%20the%20new%20Bill%20allows%20government%20agencies%20other%20than%20the%20press%20registrar%20to%20conduct%20its%20functions%2C%20which%20could%20even%20include%20police%20and%20other%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%2C%20and%20called%20the%20move%20%E2%80%9Cdeeply%20distressing%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20journalists%E2%80%99%20body%20pointed%20out%20that%20Sections%204(1)%20and%2011(4)%20of%20the%20Bill%20allow%20the%20government%20to%20deny%20the%20right%20to%20bring%20out%20a%20periodical%2C%20to%20persons%20convicted%20of%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%20act%20or%20unlawful%20activity%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20having%20done%20anything%20against%20the%20security%20of%20the%20State%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CGiven%20the%20liberal%20and%20arbitrary%20use%20of%20UAPA%2C%20as%20well%20as%20other%20criminal%20laws%2C%20including%20Sedition%2C%20against%20journalists%20and%20media%20organisations%20to%20suppress%20freedom%20of%20speech%2C%20the%20Guild%20is%20deeply%20concerned%20by%20the%20introduction%20of%20these%20new%20provisions%2C%20and%20the%20way%20they%20can%20be%20misused%20to%20deny%20the%20right%20to%20bring%20out%20news%20publications%20to%20persons%20who%20are%20critical%20of%20governments%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20also%20criticised%20the%20continuation%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20enter%20premises%20of%20news%20organisations%2C%20calling%20it%20%E2%80%9Cexcessively%20intrusive%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESection%2019%20of%20the%20Bill%20gives%20the%20Union%20government%20powers%20to%20frame%20rules%20under%20which%20news%20publishing%20is%20to%20be%20done%20in%20India.%20The%20statement%20cited%20the%20example%20of%20IT%20Rules%202021%2C%20and%20the%20latest%20amendments%20made%20to%20it%20regarding%20%E2%80%9Csetting%20up%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98fact%20checking%20unit%E2%80%99%20with%20sweeping%20powers%20to%20order%20content%20take%20down%E2%80%9D%20and%20urged%20that%20such%20rules%20be%20clearly%20defined%20in%20the%20act%20and%20not%20be%20left%20to%20the%20discretion%20of%20a%20future%20government%20or%20authority.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Guild%20said%20that%20emphasis%20of%20the%20registrar%20and%20the%20Bill%20should%20remain%20on%20%E2%80%98registration%E2%80%99%20and%20not%20%E2%80%98regulation%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20the%20latter%20could%20potentially%20restrict%20press%20freedom.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20statement%20was%20signed%20by%20president%20Seema%20Mustafa%2C%20general%20secretary%20Anant%20Nath%2C%20and%20treasurer%20Shriram%20Pawar.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691333846000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F20160312%2FUntitled-design-23-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Feditors-guild-calls-press-and-registration-of-periodicals-bill-deeply-distressing%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Guild%20said%20that%20emphasis%20of%20the%20Bill%20should%20remain%20on%20%E2%80%98registration%E2%80%99%20and%20not%20%E2%80%98regulation%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20the%20latter%20could%20potentially%20restrict%20press%20freedom.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Feditors-guild-calls-press-and-registration-of-periodicals-bill-deeply-distressing%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Barbie%E2%80%99%20R